NAME

  **env** - output environment variables

SYNOPSIS

    env 

DESCRIPTION

    The env command outputs every environment variable, and is useful for debugging. 
    Each environment variable will be output on a new line. Currently, the only 
    environment variable is PATH, by default set to `\bin`. The command takes no 
    arguments.

OPTIONS

    -h, --help:  output usage information and exit

SEE ALSO

    [ps](/data/man/ps.dsmd), [pwd](/data/man/pwd.dsmd)